<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-23T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-23T15:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3213: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United
                                        Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-23T15:00:00-05:00">December 23, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>398. Your 639, December 21, 4 p.m. You should immediately
                                    communicate orally with the Foreign Office and confirm by note
                                    as follows:</p>
                                <p>With regard to the suggestion contained in the Foreign Office
                                    note under reference, in pursuit of its uniform policy from the
                                    beginning of the Italo-Ethiopian Controversy of pursuing its own
                                    separate and independent course with respect to all phases of
                                    the matter—the American Government must reserve its
                                    most-favored-nation rights and its position with regard to any
                                    injury to American trade arising out of this or any similar
                                    arrangement which the British Government may enter into even
                                    though they be only of brief duration.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>